  "body": "<!---\r\nThanks for creating an Pull Request 💖!\r\n\r\nPlease read the following before submitting:\r\n- PRs that adds new external dependencies might take a while to review.\r\n- Keep your PR as small as possible.\r\n- Limit your PR to one type (docs, feature, refactoring, ci, or bugfix)\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n## 📝 Description\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/chakra-ui/zag/pull/1995 I added a custom component class to simplify Lit elements creation... Although this works fine as it's, a few changes can be done to improve types a little bit...\r\n\r\n## ⛳️ Current behavior (updates)\r\n\r\nIn current version, you can't access to code completion for `service` property.\r\n\r\n## 🚀 New behavior\r\n\r\nIn the new version you have a proper code completion in your IDE\r\n<img width=\"599\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-10-28 at 8 46 09 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a5038f90-0013-4415-9bdf-d1c10112608f\">\r\n\r\n\r\n## 💣 Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\n\r\n<!-- If Yes, please describe the impact and migration path for existing users. -->\r\n\r\n## 📝 Additional Information\r\n~`MachineContext` are now exported for all machines... Exposing the `MachineState could be a good addition for further use cases~\r\n",
